data.title: Yorkville Community Unit School District 115
data.text:
Yorkville Community Unit School District 115 offers educational programming to students from preschool through high school. The district encompasses 85 square-miles and serves more than 7,100 students from Yorkville, Bristol, and portions of Montgomery, Newark, Oswego, and Plano. The district is situated in a suburban/rural area approximately 50 miles southwest of Chicago. District 115 is primarily located in Kendall County, with the northern tip of the district located in Kane County.

Note: To receive current posts from the district's X (Twitter) account, please log in to your personal account through this web browser.
